		<td><b>Re: Early Joy Van/Idea-Tek/TXC Mappers</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Assuming it's a real 161... there aren't a lot of options for one by itself without extra hardware. Has to be present over the entire range from $8000-$FFFF, has to have bus conflicts, can't be anything finer than 32K PRG and/or 8K CHR.<br /><br />Without tracing, I'd guess it's mapper 148. <br /><br />(edit) ... Having now traced, I think too much information is hidden under ICs to be able to make a more informed guess. (edit2) It probably just latches the 3 LSBs of the data bus and uses them verbatim in some order as PRG A15, CHR A13, and CHRA14. Possibly the same order as mapper 133?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


